Orange Customer Retention

Introduction

Technology is fast changing and so are the customers needs. We have seen a shift from SMS and Call to purely Data interactions. In this paper we examine a telecommunications company Orange and its competitors and answer the question: What makes a customer stay as an Orange subscriber?

We will help Orange maximize profit and prevent attrition by finding out the reasons why customers stay. Hence, we will use Principal Component Analysis and Clustering techniques in order to identify the importance features of a telco data and identifying typical postpaid customer behavior.

We will particularly use PCA to differentiate the major sources of variations in the data, simplify the data by describing customer behavior with fewer features and identify atypical behaviors. On the other hand, we will be using Cluster Analysis to suggest several prototypes of behavior existing in the data and describe how each prototype is related to churning.

Finally, we will be applying regularization in order to construct an interpretable and actionable model that predicts which customer are likely to churn after two months. We will also be discussing potential indicators or warning signals for customer churn.

Background

There are different reasons in addition to bad service why customers leave a network, in Oranges case, with its flexible plan offers, it brings certain costs. Some customers leave because they might have gotten the wrong subscription and miscalculated the consumption and thus might result to a failed payment. In other scenarios, a better alternative might have been chosen by the customer, in which it can be observed by increasing texts to other telco providers and by the declining calls, SMS, and data usage.

Data Preparation and Framework

  1. Data Preprocessing -we have done some data reduction techniques for monthly variables and reduced 5 month data into sums, differences, and average. From 99 variables, we have redeced it to 29 variables by data reduction techniques

    • Usage Trend - difference in usage between 1st month of subscription vs.5th month of subscription(SMS, Call, Data)

    • Actual vs Plan Used - Difference in set data plan vs mean 5-month actual plan usage

    • 5 month Sum - SMS Call Data consumed, SMS revenue, Call Revenue, Data Revenue, Onnet Revenue and Offnet revenue

  2. Cluster Analysis - we have done a boxplot visualisation and Selected variables that have noticeable difference on values between being churned or not

We have reduced the variables from 98 to 27 variables, excluding categorical data which are churn and location.

Looking at the high loadings on the PC rotation, we can summarize the major sources of variation into 8 components:

We categorize these eight principal components and namely

  1. PC1= Low Call These users have low calls for Orange, Lemon, and Berry networks as well low call for the last 5 months, thus low call offnet revenue.

  2. PC2: Low SMS: These users have low SMS for Orange, Lemon, and Berry, low SMS revenue, low SMS for the last 5 months however, they have a high call plan

3.PC3: Low Data Plan Low Data User : These users planned their their data plan correctly and most like have WiFi in their homes/offices

  1. ** PC4: Low SMS Plan, Overused Call minutes**: These are also subscribers that has miscalculated their call plans.

  2. PC5: Overused Data : These users have overused their allotted data plan

6.** PC6: Overused SMS and Decreasing Call**: These users has overused their SMS plan threshold and we also saw decreasing call trend for the past 5 months

  1. PC7:Underused SMS and Old Network Age : Probably old users who avails an SMS plan

  2. PC8: Low Number of Registration to Other Promo , high service calls, increasing data users.: Users who are enjoying the data plan.

Clustering the data into 4 gets mixed results. Picking two clusters, we see a better clustering. 2-Means clustering shows that cluster 1 has more network age, uses less service calls, uses more sms and used more than the plan threshold for SMS, had more calls for the past 5 months but aalmost same data usage across 5 months. Moreover, the user has increasing data needs and has more more offnet revenue compared to cluster 2.

We can see that among the two, characteristics of customers in cluster 1 is more susceptible to churning because, although the customers in this cluster has the same data usage for the past months, we can see that the offnet revenue is strikingly higher than cluster 2. This means that customers are availing more calls and sms to other networks. In which the increasing SMS and calls results agree.

For one one unit increase in service calls, the odds of a churned account vs non-churned account increases by 1.0170 For one one unit increase in the difference of actual SMS Actual from the SMS registered amount SMS, the odds of a churned account vs non-churned account increases by 1.4121 For one one unit gincrease in the five month SMS usage, the odds of a churned account vs non-churned account decreases by 0.9664 For one one unit increase in the difference of actual Data used from the registered data amount , the odds of a churned account vs non-churned account increases by 1.7263

Conclusion

After doing some exploration on customer data and running PCA, cluster analysis, and model builiding with regularization. We have seen that we can reduce 97 variables into 8 reduced one by PCA and categorize the by Low Calls, Low SMS, Low Data Plan and Low Data, Low SMS and Overused Calls, Overused data, Underused SMS and Old Network Age, and Low Number of Registration to Other Promo , high service calls, increasing data users.

Moreover using cluster Analysis, we have seen that the first cluster, in which customers have a noticeable difference on cluster 2 which. Cluster1 has has been with the network longer, uses less service calls, uses more sms and used more than the plan threshold for SMS, had more calls for the past 5 months but almost same data usage across 5 months. Moreover, the user has increasing data needs and has more more offnet revenue compared to cluster 2. Based on the comparison, customers on the first quarter are interacting with more calls and sms outside the network. It is recommended to offer more promos that offers text to other other networks

Based on the model that we generated, we can see that a lasso model picked variables for churning prediction. We can see that a higher number of service call results to a higher odds of churning, thus it is best to keep customer service helpful to get through customers from their issues. Moreover an overused SMS usage from the SMS plan and a decreasing trend in SMS usage is also a sign of churning. Additional data used from set plan also increases the odds of churning. Thus, it recommended for orange to keep their offers in SMS and Data up to data to keep their customers up to date. A cheaper data plan and SMS offer would prevent their customers from not being able to pay in time and at the same time not explore other options.
